See http://luddite.cst.usyd.edu.au/UQ/Ethics-lecture-notes  for lecture handouts.

- course textbooks, available from the bookshop:
-- Simon Blackburn, _Ethics: A Very Short Introduction_
-- James Rachel, _The Elements of Moral Philosophy_, 4th edition (not available yet)

UQEthics.WeeklyExplanationExamples

- further reading:
-- AModestProposal
-- Iain M. Banks, _Complicity_ (a novel)
-- Harry J. Gensler, _Ethics: A contemporary introduction_ (very easy)
-- Gordon Graham, _Eight Theories of Ethics_
-- Louis P. Pojman, _Ethics: Discovering Right and Wrong_
-- Joseph P. ..DeMarco, _Moral Theory: A Contemporary Overview_

- good web starting points
-- the Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy: http://plato.stanford.edu/contents.html
--- http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/ethics-virtue/

- on normative versus descriptive statements in ethics, Wikipedia is good ... and you can have fun editing it!  See:
-- http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normative
-- http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normative_ethics
-- http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Descriptive_ethics

- contractarianism:
-- http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/contractarianism
-- http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/hobbes-moral

Watch this space for new suggestions as the semester goes on.

